I'll admit it: I'm not a huge fan of hiking. However, if I were going to be persuaded to go, I'd go here, to Mount Inwang (or, more commonly known in Korea as Inwangsan). The mountain is located in Seoul's Seochon neighborhood, which makes it a perfect place to go hike off some steam after a day of lazy cafe reading. If you're like me and hiking isn't your thing, let your friends do the steep climbing and enjoy the park around the base of the mountain, which is quite beautiful. For those going to the peak, be warned: The trail is steep and treacherous at points, and all of the old Koreans will definitely be faster than you.
